	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-19T03:34:33">BAE Systems plc is a defense, aerospace and security company. The Company operates in five segments: Electronic Systems, which consists of the Company's United States and United Kingdom-based electronics activities; Cyber &amp; Intelligence, which comprises of its United States-based Intelligence &amp; Security business and United Kingdom-headquartered Applied Intelligence business, and covers the Company's cyber, secure government, and commercial and financial security activities; Platforms &amp; Services (United States), which comprises its United States-headquartered Land &amp; Armaments business, and the United States-based services and sustainment activities; Platforms &amp; Services (United Kingdom), which comprises its United Kingdom -based air, maritime, combat vehicle, munitions and shared services activities, and Platforms &amp; Services (International), which comprises the Company's businesses in Saudi Arabia, Australia and Oman, together with its 37.5% interest in the MBDA joint venture.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-18T07:30:57">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 31 December 2015, BAE Systems plc revenues increased 9% to L16.79B. Net income increased 24% to L918M. Revenues reflect investments increase of 8% to L17.9B, Share of Sales of Equity Accoutned Inves increase of 7% to -L1.12B. Net income benefited from Remeasurement of Fianancial Instrument increase of 69% to L167M (income), Share of results of equity accounted inv increase of 33% to L110M (income).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
